Spain’s Salgado Calls for Fast Approval of EFSF Overhaul

-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 
2011-09-16T06:11:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/correct-spain-s-salgado-says-efsf-leveraging-can-t-go-too-fast.html
European parliaments should work to
approve the July 21 financial reform passage as quickly as
possible, Spanish Finance Minister  Elena Salgado  told reporters
at a meeting in Wroclaw,  Poland .  At the same time, she said “we can’t go too fast” on
leveraging the rescue fund to increase its firepower. “What is
important is that all participants approve as quickly as
possible,” she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
